17/12/2006
WASHINGTON, United States -- The IMF board on Saturday (December 16th) endorsed Montenegro's membership in the financial institution. 
An official ceremony will be held Monday in Washington. 
Podgorica had to apply for membership in the Fund after splitting from its former state union with Serbia.
In another story, Podgorica announced on Saturday that Montenegro and the Vatican would formally launch bilateral diplomatic ties. 
The two sides reached an agreement to set up embassies and promote friendly relations. 
(Pobjeda - 17/12/06; Mina - 16/12/06)
